<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>
        <%= title %>
    </title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
</head>

<body>
    <%- include('partials/header') %>

        <div class="container mt-4">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                            <h4 class="mb-0">About the Scraper API</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h5>What is this?</h5>
                            <p>
                                This is a Node.js API for extracting product details from e-commerce websites.
                                It currently supports Flipkart, Amazon India, and Myntra.
                            </p>

                            <h5>API Usage</h5>
                            <p>The API provides a single endpoint for scraping product details:</p>

                            <div class="card bg-light mb-3">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h6>Endpoint: GET /product</h6>
                                    <p><strong>Query Parameters:</strong></p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><code>url</code> (required): Full URL of the product page from a supported
                                            website</li>
                                    </ul>

                                    <p><strong>Example Request:</strong></p>
                                    <pre><code>GET http://localhost:3000/product?url=https://www.flipkart.com/product-page</code></pre>

                                    <p><strong>Example Response:</strong></p>
                                    <pre><code>{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "title": "Product Name",
    "price": "â‚¹1,999",
    "availability": "In Stock",
    "description": "Product description text...",
    "image_url": "https://example.com/image.jpg"
  }
}</code></pre>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <h5>Features</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Extracts structured product data (title, price, availability, description, image
                                    URL)</li>
                                <li>Handles redirects and shortened URLs</li>
                                <li>Uses headless browser for JavaScript-heavy sites</li>
                                <li>Rate-limiting to prevent abuse</li>
                                <li>Robust error handling</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h5>Technologies Used</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Node.js and Express.js</li>
                                <li>Cheerio for HTML parsing</li>
                                <li>Puppeteer for headless browser scraping</li>
                                <li>Axios for HTTP requests</li>
                                <li>EJS for templating</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <%- include('partials/footer') %>

            <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
            <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
</body>

</html>